# Netlify / GitHub Pages redirect rules
# Enforce www canonical and HTTPS via server-side 301 redirects

# Non-www → www (301 permanent)
https://fullonbaan.com/*   https://www.fullonbaan.com/:splat  301!

# HTTP → HTTPS (GitHub Pages enforces HTTPS natively when "Enforce HTTPS" is enabled in repo settings)
# For Netlify:
http://fullonbaan.com/*    https://www.fullonbaan.com/:splat  301!
http://www.fullonbaan.com/* https://www.fullonbaan.com/:splat 301!

# Legacy Blogspot pages → relevant new pages (301 permanent)
/2012/*    https://www.fullonbaan.com/about/     301!
/2016/*    https://www.fullonbaan.com/services/   301!
/2017/*    https://www.fullonbaan.com/services/   301!
/2020/*    https://www.fullonbaan.com/training/   301!
